    comment: '<p>The HTML <code>&#x3C;abbr></code>, or the <strong>Abbreviation</strong> element, is used to represent an abbreviation. The element has a <code>title</code> attribute which can provide a full description of the abbreviation and nothing else.</p>\n<p>The content of the title is often shown in a tooltip when a user hovers over the element.  Also, some browsers add a dotted underline to the content of the element.</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;p>\n  Learn all about\n  &#x3C;abbr\n    title="HyperText Markup Language">\n    HTML\n  &#x3C;/abbr>\n  using Enki.\n&#x3C;/p>\n</code></pre>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="56"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="56" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="Roboto-Regular, Roboto" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="34">Learn all about HTML using Enki.</tspan></text><path stroke="#000" stroke-dasharray="1 2" stroke-linecap="square" d="M129.5 36.5h45"/></g></svg></p>\n<!--[View Codepen](https://codepen.io/enkidevs/pen/rrjOGv)-->\n<p>By default, the <code>&#x3C;abbr></code> element is displayed as an inline element.</p>\n<p>The <code>&#x3C;abbr></code> element can also be styled with appropriate CSS properties.</p>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="320" height="56"><defs><path id="a" d="M0 0h18v18H0z"/><path id="c" d="M0 0h18v18H0z"/><path id="e" d="M0 0h18v18H0z"/><path id="g" d="M0 0h18v18H0z"/><path id="i" d="M0 0h18v18H0z"/><path id="k" d="M0 0h18v18H0z"/></defs><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="56" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><path stroke="#E37C00" stroke-dasharray="1 2" stroke-linecap="square" d="M129.5 36.5h45"/><text font-family="Roboto-Regular, Roboto" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="34" fill="#000">Learn all about </tspan> <tspan x="129.23438" y="34" fill="#E37C00">HTML</tspan> <tspan x="172.53906" y="34" fill="#000"> using Enki.</tspan></text><g tran